args:
Fear of abandonment sends Tiki into a panic,
but Mym risks her life to convince her that she
isn't alone. The gambit works, and Tiki soon
returns to her old self.
I'm scared... Don't leave me alone!\nWhy does everyone abandon me?!
Don't leave me! I'll do anything!
I don't want to be alooone!
Now I see why you call her a ＂divine＂\ndragon. How can we hope to stop\nsuch a powerful creature?
Aw, I feel bad for her. Poor kid seems to\nbe locked inside some kinda nightmare.
Yes, of course... To her, this strange world\nof ours WOULD be akin to a nightmare!
I heard rumors of a golden dragon that was\nspotted during an imperial dragon hunt.
The creature had apparently been fighting\nto protect the local dragons.
Now it all makes sense! She saw imperial\nsoldiers hunting dragons and decided that\nall humans must be her enemy!
There's likely more to it than that.
Tiki's tribe of Divine Dragons\nhas been all but exterminated.
And witnessing the other dragons being\nslaughtered may have triggered her fear\nof being abandoned once more.
The fear of being left behind...\nThe loneliness of isolation... \nI know just how she feels.
Oh, it's all just so heartbreaking.
Okay, so we all agree we feel terrible,\nbut we ALSO can't just let her run wild\nand tear up the joint! So what's the plan?
All we have to do is show her that she\nISN'T alone. Now just stand back and\nleave all of this to me, darling!
It's all right. Everything is all right.\nYour name is Tiki, yes?
If you're looking for companionship,\nTiki, you can find it here.
I wish I could say we are the same,\nbut I'm neither divine, nor a manakete.
So you're not like me...?\nI knew it. I knew I was alone.
While it's true you and I are different,\nthat doesn't mean you're alone.
My kind are also called dragons, you see,\nand we also differ from humans.

To be honest, there are times when I find
them both exhausting and infuriating.
Nevertheless, there are many of their
number that I am proud to call friend.
Think, Tiki. Surely you have people\nsuch as that in your life as well.
See? You DO have people like that!\nAnd so long as you remember them,\nthat means you're not alone.
I...remember now. I have lots of friends. \nI'm not alone... I was never alone!
I believe she has fallen asleep.
Awww, she's adorable! I bet if we had a\ndaughter, she'd be just like that, darling.\nDon't you agree?
I know Tiki looks young, but she's actually\nvery, very old. I think she may have too\nmany years on her to be called a child.
Oh, really? Well, I suppose dragons are\nlike that sometimes.
Yes, I'm pretty sure she's almost a\nthousand years old.
A THOUSAND?! That means this child is\nolder than ME!
N-nothing is wrong! The nice dragon lady\nis just fine, thank you very much!
